 Purpose:
MySQL-compatible relational database providing persistent storage for WordPress (posts, pages, users, comments, settings).

Access Information:
- URL: N/A (internal database - no web interface)
- Port(s): (internal only - not exposed externally)
- Location (VM): apps.lab.local
- Container/Service Name: mariadb

Credentials:
- Admin Username: root
- Admin Password Location: Stored in Vaultwarden

Technical Details:
- Database: MariaDB 10.11
- Configuration Files: /opt/docker/mariadb/ (if custom config exists)
- Data Location: /opt/docker/mariadb-data/ (or Docker volume 'mariadb-data')
- Log Location: docker logs mariadb

Common Operations:

Restart:
docker compose restart mariadb

View Logs:
docker logs mariadb -f

Check Status:
docker ps | grep mariadb
docker exec mariadb mysqladmin -u root -p ping

Backup:
docker exec mariadb mysqldump -u root -pPASSWORD wordpress > /opt/backups/wordpress-db-$(date +%Y%m%d).sql

Dependencies:
- Requires: None (standalone database)
- Required by: WordPress (cannot function without database)

Notes:
- Contains WordPress database named “wordpress”
- Critical data - backup regularly
- Do NOT delete without backing up first
- Restore: docker exec -i mariadb mysql -u root -pPASSWORD wordpress < backup.sql
